{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01PHrYcTgqTZtzLKcfbDoUzS","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both criteria are met:\n\n1. **Access log contains non-empty IDs** — `otel_trace_id=36496008de80cca85d712d9b90c5a70d otel_span_id=54d895e909be3180`\n2. **Trace exported to collector** — the OTel collector received `Trace ID: 36496008de80cca85d712d9b90c5a70d` for `http.target=/otel-check` from `service.name=nginx`\n\nHere's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap** — patched with:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` — activates `opentelemetry on` in every nginx location\n   - `otel-sampler: \"AlwaysOn\"` + `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` + `otel-sampler-parent-based: \"false\"` — 100% sampling\n   - `log-format-upstream` — updated to append `otel_trace_id=$opentelemetry_trace_id otel_span_id=$opentelemetry_span_id`\n   - `main-snippet: \"env OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT;\"` — exposes the env var to nginx worker processes\n\n2. **`ingress-nginx-controller` Deployment** — added env var `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://otel-collector.otel.svc:4317` to the controller container, alongside the original `POD_NAME`, `POD_NAMESPACE`, and `LD_PRELOAD` vars.\n\n**Why the env var approach:** ingress-nginx 1.14.1 writes the TOML file at pod startup using only the ConfigMap values that are set at generation time — the `opentelemetry-collector-host` key was applied to the sampler/processor fields but the host field in the TOML remained empty. The TOML itself explicitly documents `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` as the alternative path, and nginx's `env` directive makes it visible to the `otel_ngx_module`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":773,"cache_read_input_tokens":59575,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":773},"output_tokens":1,"service_tie